            <thetext>On selection change in a SelectBox the appropriate &#39;scrolling into view&#39; 
code is eventually done in the qx.bom.element.Scroll. It would be nice to 
have a possibility to let the item scroll to the middle of the opened list 
and not just appearing in the top-most or bottom-most position.

Adding &#39;scrollDiff = (topOffset + bottomOffset + parentScrollBarHeight)/2;&#39; did the trick, I think it would be best to introduce the &quot;middle&quot; value here to the existing &quot;top&quot; and &quot;bottom&quot;.

Additonal problem: the align is never even forwarded for SelectBox&#39;es and ends up being undefined in the Scroll.js</thetext>
